{"declarations":[{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticBlock_until_cancelled_\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Test</span>.<span class=\"name\">Cancel</span>.<span class=\"name\">tacticBlock_until_cancelled_</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Tactic for testing cancellation propagation. On the first invocation for a given `<label>`,\nprints `<label>: blocked` to stderr, resolves the sync promise `<label>` (so a separate\ntheorem can gate the runner's `waitFor` on this invocation having actually started), and\nloops on `Core.checkInterrupted` until the tactic's cancel token fires (at which point the\nloop throws and `finally` resolves the shared task). Subsequent invocations (e.g. on\nre-elaboration) wait on that task: they return as soon as the first invocation has actually\nexited the loop, and hang otherwise. So if cancellation propagates correctly, the test\ncompletes; if propagation is broken, the second invocation's wait blocks forever and the\ntest hangs (timeout = failure).\n","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticBlock_until_cancelled_","kind":"def","line":285,"name":"Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticBlock_until_cancelled_","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.lean#L285-L296"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticWait_for_sync_\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Test</span>.<span class=\"name\">Cancel</span>.<span class=\"name\">tacticWait_for_sync_</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Block until `resolveSyncPromise label` has been called. Direct `IO.wait`, no polling. ","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticWait_for_sync_","kind":"def","line":275,"name":"Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticWait_for_sync_","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.lean#L275-L276"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.resolveSyncPromise\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Test</span>.<span class=\"name\">Cancel</span>.<span class=\"name\">resolveSyncPromise</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">label</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#String\">String</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#BaseIO\">BaseIO</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Resolve the sync promise for `label`. Idempotent (subsequent resolves are no-ops). ","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.resolveSyncPromise","kind":"def","line":271,"name":"Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.resolveSyncPromise","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.lean#L271-L273"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.getSyncPromise\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Test</span>.<span class=\"name\">Cancel</span>.<span class=\"name\">getSyncPromise</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">label</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#String\">String</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#BaseIO\">BaseIO</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/System/Promise.html#IO.Promise\">IO.Promise</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Return the sync promise for `label`, creating it if no entry exists. All callers\nreceive the same promise. ","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.getSyncPromise","kind":"def","line":262,"name":"Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.getSyncPromise","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.lean#L262-L269"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.syncPromisesRef\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Test</span>.<span class=\"name\">Cancel</span>.<span class=\"name\">syncPromisesRef</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#IO.Ref\">IO.Ref</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Std/Data/HashMap/Basic.html#Std.HashMap\">Std.HashMap</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#String\">String</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/System/Promise.html#IO.Promise\">IO.Promise</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a>)</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Registry of label-keyed `IO.Promise Unit` for synchronization between cooperating\ntactics/elaborators in tests. The promise is kept alive by the ref itself, so\n`prom.result?` only fires on explicit `resolveSyncPromise` -- there is no drop signal.\nDistinct from `testTasksRef`, which stores only the `Task` side and relies on caller\nliveness to detect dropped-without-resolved. ","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.syncPromisesRef","kind":"opaque","line":255,"name":"Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.syncPromisesRef","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.lean#L255-L260"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticWait_for_test_task_\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Test</span>.<span class=\"name\">Cancel</span>.<span class=\"name\">tacticWait_for_test_task_</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Block until the test task named `label` fires. Prints a diagnostic to stderr if\nthe underlying promise was dropped without resolution, or if no task is registered for\n`label`. The diagnostic uses stderr rather than `throwError` so that the failure is\nvisible even when this tactic is evaluated inside `try?` (or any other combinator that\nswallows tactic errors). ","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticWait_for_test_task_","kind":"def","line":238,"name":"Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticWait_for_test_task_","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.lean#L238-L243"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.mkTestTask\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Test</span>.<span class=\"name\">Cancel</span>.<span class=\"name\">mkTestTask</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\">\n<span class=\"fn\">(<span class=\"fn\">label</span> : <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#String\">String</a>)</span></span>\n<span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#BaseIO\">BaseIO</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/System/Promise.html#IO.Promise\">IO.Promise</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a>)</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Register a fresh test task under `label`, returning the underlying `IO.Promise`.\nReturns `none` if a task is already registered under `label`. The caller is responsible\nfor keeping the returned promise alive and arranging its resolution -- typically by\ncapturing it in a `cancelTk.onSet` closure that calls `prom.resolve`. ","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.mkTestTask","kind":"def","line":229,"name":"Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.mkTestTask","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.lean#L229-L236"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.testTasksRef\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Test</span>.<span class=\"name\">Cancel</span>.<span class=\"name\">testTasksRef</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#IO.Ref\">IO.Ref</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Std/Data/HashMap/Basic.html#Std.HashMap\">Std.HashMap</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#String\">String</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Task\">Task</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a>)</span>)</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Registry of label-keyed `Task (Option Unit)` values for use by `mkTestTask` and\n`wait_for_test_task`. The stored task is `prom.result?` of the promise returned by\n`mkTestTask`; the registry itself does not keep that promise alive, so if no other\nreference exists, the promise drops and the task fires `none`. ","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.testTasksRef","kind":"opaque","line":223,"name":"Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.testTasksRef","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.lean#L223-L227"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.commandWait_for_cancel_once_command_\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Test</span>.<span class=\"name\">Cancel</span>.<span class=\"name\">commandWait_for_cancel_once_command_</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Like `wait_for_main_cancel_once_async` but for commands. Takes a `num` parameter so that its syntax\ncan be changed (via `change:`) to trigger re-elaboration. Sends \"blocked\" as a diagnostic and spawns\nan async task that waits for the command's cancellation token to be set.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.commandWait_for_cancel_once_command_","kind":"def","line":197,"name":"Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.commandWait_for_cancel_once_command_","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.lean#L197-L202"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.cmdOnceRef\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Test</span>.<span class=\"name\">Cancel</span>.<span class=\"name\">cmdOnceRef</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#IO.Ref\">IO.Ref</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Task\">Task</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a>)</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.cmdOnceRef","kind":"opaque","line":195,"name":"Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.cmdOnceRef","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.lean#L195-L195"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticWait_for_main_cancel_once_async\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Test</span>.<span class=\"name\">Cancel</span>.<span class=\"name\">tacticWait_for_main_cancel_once_async</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Like `wait_for_cancel_once_async` but waits for the main thread's cancellation token. This is useful\nto test main thread cancellation in non-incremental contexts because we otherwise wouldn't be able\nto send out the \"blocked\" message from there.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticWait_for_main_cancel_once_async","kind":"def","line":163,"name":"Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticWait_for_main_cancel_once_async","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.lean#L163-L168"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticWait_for_cancel_once_async\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Test</span>.<span class=\"name\">Cancel</span>.<span class=\"name\">tacticWait_for_cancel_once_async</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Like `wait_for_cancel_once` but does the waiting in a separate task and waits for its\ncancellation.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticWait_for_cancel_once_async","kind":"def","line":131,"name":"Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticWait_for_cancel_once_async","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.lean#L131-L135"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticUnblock\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Test</span>.<span class=\"name\">Cancel</span>.<span class=\"name\">tacticUnblock</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Unblocks a `wait_for_unblock*` task. ","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticUnblock","kind":"def","line":126,"name":"Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticUnblock","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.lean#L126-L129"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticWait_for_unblock_async\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Test</span>.<span class=\"name\">Cancel</span>.<span class=\"name\">tacticWait_for_unblock_async</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Spawns a `logSnapshotTask` that waits for `unblock` to be called, which is expected to happen in a\nsubsequent document version that does not invalidate this tactic. Complains if cancellation token\nwas set before unblocking, i.e. if the tactic was invalidated after all.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticWait_for_unblock_async","kind":"def","line":104,"name":"Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticWait_for_unblock_async","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.lean#L104-L124"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticWait_for_unblock\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Test</span>.<span class=\"name\">Cancel</span>.<span class=\"name\">tacticWait_for_unblock</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"Waits for `unblock` to be called, which is expected to happen in a subsequent document version that\ndoes not invalidate this tactic. Complains if cancellation token was set before unblocking, i.e. if\nthe tactic was invalidated after all.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticWait_for_unblock","kind":"def","line":74,"name":"Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticWait_for_unblock","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.lean#L74-L79"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.unblockedCancelTkRef\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Test</span>.<span class=\"name\">Cancel</span>.<span class=\"name\">unblockedCancelTkRef</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#IO.Ref\">IO.Ref</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <a href=\"./Init/System/CancelToken.html#IO.CancelToken\">IO.CancelToken</a>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.unblockedCancelTkRef","kind":"opaque","line":66,"name":"Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.unblockedCancelTkRef","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.lean#L66-L66"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">def</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticWait_for_cancel_once\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Test</span>.<span class=\"name\">Cancel</span>.<span class=\"name\">tacticWait_for_cancel_once</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Lean.ParserDescr\">ParserDescr</a></div></div>","info":{"doc":"On first invocation, sends a diagnostics \"blocked\", blocks until cancelled, and then eprints\n\"cancelled!\"; further invocations complete when this wait is done but do not wait for their own\ncancellation. Thus all document versions should complete strictly after the printing has completed\nand we avoid terminating the server too early to see the message.\n","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticWait_for_cancel_once","kind":"def","line":26,"name":"Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.tacticWait_for_cancel_once","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.lean#L26-L32"}},{"header":"<div class=\"decl_header\"><span class=\"decl_kind\">opaque</span>\n<span class=\"decl_name\"><a class=\"break_within\" href=\"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.onceRef\"><span class=\"name\">Lean</span>.<span class=\"name\">Server</span>.<span class=\"name\">Test</span>.<span class=\"name\">Cancel</span>.<span class=\"name\">onceRef</span></a></span><span class=\"decl_args\"> :</span><div class=\"decl_type\"><span class=\"fn\"><a href=\"./Init/System/IO.html#IO.Ref\">IO.Ref</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Option\">Option</a> <span class=\"fn\">(<a href=\"./Init/Core.html#Task\">Task</a> <a href=\"./Init/Prelude.html#Unit\">Unit</a>)</span>)</span></span></div></div>","info":{"doc":"","docLink":"./Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.html#Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.onceRef","kind":"opaque","line":24,"name":"Lean.Server.Test.Cancel.onceRef","sourceLink":"https://github.com/leanprover/lean4/blob/62eed1db4d67327ec8120be05f1a1b0847d74561/src/Lean/Server/Test/Cancel.lean#L24-L24"}}],"imports":["Lean.Elab.Command","Lean.Elab.Tactic.Basic"],"instances":[],"name":"Lean.Server.Test.Cancel"}